8. DEPLOYMENT & OPERATIONS

8.1 Deployment Models

```yaml
cloud_native:
  platforms: AWS, Azure, GCP, Oracle Cloud
  orchestration: Kubernetes (K8s 1.28+)
  service_mesh: Istio or Linkerd
  scaling: Horizontal Pod Autoscaler + Cluster Autoscaler

hybrid_edge:
  edge_nodes: Minimum 4-core, 16GB RAM, 100GB storage
  synchronization: CRDT-based eventual consistency
  offline_operation: 24-hour autonomous operation capability

on_premises:
  requirements: VMware/OpenStack virtualization
  minimum_cluster: 3 control nodes + 5 worker nodes
  air_gap: Full disconnected operation support
```

8.2 Monitoring & Observability

```
Metrics Collection:
- Pillar health: 1000+ metrics per pillar
- Business metrics: Customizable KPI mapping
- Resource utilization: Fine-grained per-component

Tracing:
- Distributed tracing: W3C Trace Context standard
- Span collection: 100% sampling for error paths, 1% for success
- Trace retention: 30 days hot, 1 year cold

Logging:
- Structured JSON logging with unified schema
- Log aggregation: Loki or Elasticsearch
- Retention: 90 days operational, 7 years compliance
```

8.3 SLOs & SLAs

```
Service Level Objectives (per pillar):
- Availability: 99.95% (excluding planned maintenance)
- Latency: P95 < 200ms for critical paths
- Throughput: Sustained at 80% of peak capacity
- Data Freshness: <1 second for real-time streams

Service Level Agreements:
- Incident Response: <15 minutes for critical issues
- Resolution Time: <4 hours for high severity
- Data Recovery: RPO=1 minute, RTO=5 minutes
- Support: 24/7 with 15-minute escalation paths
```

