9. INTEGRATION & EXTENSIBILITY

9.1 Integration Patterns

```
API-based:
- REST/GraphQL/gRPC interfaces
- Webhook subscriptions for events
- SDKs: Python, Java, Go, JavaScript

Message-based:
- Kafka topic subscriptions
- AWS SNS/SQS, Azure Service Bus
- MQTT for IoT edge integration

Data Pipeline:
- Airflow, Dagster, Prefect operators
- dbt transformations
- Change Data Capture (CDC) connectors
```

9.2 Extension Framework

```python
# Example: Custom healing action
@seraph_plugin(action_type="healing", version="1.0")
class DatabaseConnectionHealer:
    def diagnose(self, symptoms: List[Symptom]) -> Diagnosis:
        # Custom diagnosis logic
        return Diagnosis(...)
    
    def execute(self, params: Dict) -> ActionResult:
        # Custom healing logic
        return ActionResult(...)
    
    def validate(self) -> ValidationResult:
        # Safety validation
        return ValidationResult(...)
```

9.3 Pre-built Connectors

· Cloud: AWS, Azure, GCP full suite
· Databases: PostgreSQL, MySQL, MongoDB, Redis, Elasticsearch
· Monitoring: Prometheus, Datadog, New Relic, Splunk
· Identity: Okta, Azure AD, Ping Identity, Keycloak
· Message Queues: RabbitMQ, ActiveMQ, Apache Pulsar

